# SYN'TEK LANGUAGE LICENSE
## Version 1.0 — February 19, 2026

---

# SYNTEK CREATIVE OWNERSHIP LICENSE (SCOL v1.0)

**Copyright © 2026 Julien Maurel. All Rights Reserved.**

---

## PREAMBLE

This license governs the use, modification, distribution, and contribution
to the **Syn'Tek Language** (hereinafter "the Language"), including but
not limited to: its syntax, grammar rules, operators, semantic tokens,
dictionary, phonetic system, sentence structures, expansion packs,
documentation, field manuals, wiki content, and all associated
intellectual property.

The Language was **solely created, designed, and developed by
Julien Maurel** (hereinafter "the Creator"), originating from Mauritius.

This license exists to:
1. Protect the Creator's exclusive intellectual property rights
2. Allow the global community to use and improve the Language
3. Prevent any person or entity from claiming ownership or creatorship
4. Ensure the Language remains open for use but owned by its Creator

---

## ARTICLE 1 — DEFINITIONS

**1.1 "The Language"** refers to Syn'Tek in its entirety: all syntax rules,
operators (::, >>, //, !), semantic tokens, dictionary entries, grammar
rules, phonetic guides, number systems, time systems, domain expansions
(PULSE, VITA, OPS, WARZONE, CYPHER, TERRA, SIGNAL, CLASSIFIED), example
sentences, field manuals, wiki pages, and any future additions to the
Syn'Tek ecosystem.

**1.2 "The Creator"** refers exclusively to **Julien Maurel**, the sole
author, inventor, and intellectual property owner of the Language.

**1.3 "User"** refers to any individual, group, organization, company,
or artificial intelligence system that uses, studies, teaches, speaks,
writes, or interacts with the Language.

**1.4 "Contributor"** (also "Prime") refers to any User who submits new
tokens, rules, examples, translations, or improvements to the Language.

**1.5 "Contribution"** refers to any addition, modification, translation,
expansion, or improvement submitted to the Language by a Contributor.

**1.6 "Derivative Work"** refers to any project, product, service,
application, or work that is built upon, incorporates, or is substantially
based on the Language.

**1.7 "Commercial Use"** refers to any use of the Language intended to
generate revenue, profit, or commercial advantage, whether directly or
indirectly.

---

## ARTICLE 2 — INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY & OWNERSHIP

**2.1 Sole Creatorship.**
Julien Maurel is the sole and exclusive creator of the Syn'Tek Language.
No person, entity, organization, company, or artificial intelligence may
claim to have created, co-created, invented, or co-invented the Language,
in whole or in part.

**2.2 Exclusive Ownership.**
All intellectual property rights, including but not limited to copyright,
moral rights, trademark rights, patent rights, and trade secret rights
pertaining to the Language belong exclusively and perpetually to
Julien Maurel.

**2.3 Moral Rights.**
The Creator retains all moral rights over the Language, including:
- The right of attribution (to be identified as the Creator)
- The right of integrity (to object to derogatory treatment)
- The right of disclosure (to decide when and how the Language is published)

These moral rights are **inalienable, non-transferable, and perpetual**.

**2.4 Name & Brand Protection.**
The names "Syn'Tek", "SynTek", "Syn-Tek", "SYNTEK", and all variations
thereof, as well as associated logos, symbols, and branding elements, are
the exclusive property of Julien Maurel. No person or entity may register
these as trademarks, domain names, social media handles, or brand names
without the Creator's explicit written authorization.

**2.5 No Transfer of Ownership.**
This license does NOT transfer any ownership rights to any User or
Contributor. Users receive a license to USE the Language, not to OWN it.

---

## ARTICLE 3 — GRANTED RIGHTS (What Users CAN Do)

Subject to the terms of this license, the Creator grants all Users a
**worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free, non-transferable, revocable
license** to:

**3.1 Use.**
Users may use the Language for any purpose, including but not limited to:
- Personal communication (spoken and written)
- Education and teaching
- Research and academic study
- Creative writing, fiction, and worldbuilding
- AI training and prompt engineering
- Software development and integration
- Community building and discussion

**3.2 Learn & Teach.**
Users may learn, study, practice, and teach the Language to others,
provided that:
- The Creator is always credited as the sole inventor
- This license is referenced in any teaching materials
- No teacher or institution claims ownership of the Language

**3.3 Contribute & Improve.**
Users may submit new tokens, rules, examples, translations, expansions,
and improvements to the Language through the official contribution
process (Pull Requests on the official repository), subject to Article 5.

**3.4 Share & Distribute.**
Users may share, copy, and distribute the Language documentation,
provided that:
- This license is included in full with any distribution
- The Creator is credited as sole inventor
- The content is not modified in a way that misrepresents the Creator's
  work or intentions
- No fee is charged for the Language itself (see Article 4 for
  Commercial Use)

**3.5 Create Derivative Works.**
Users may create tools, applications, plugins, translators, dictionaries,
bots, and other works that USE the Language, provided that:
- The derivative work clearly states: "Based on Syn'Tek, created by
  Julien Maurel"
- The derivative work does not claim to BE the Language or to replace it
- This license is referenced in the derivative work's documentation

**3.6 Fork & Modify.**
Users may fork the official repository and create modified versions for
personal or experimental use, provided that:
- Modified versions are clearly labeled as "Modified" or "Unofficial"
- Modified versions do NOT use the name "Syn'Tek" without the prefix
  "Modified" or "Unofficial" or a clearly different name
- The original Creator is credited in all modified versions
- Modified versions include this license in full

---

## ARTICLE 4 — COMMERCIAL USE

**4.1 Non-Commercial Use: Free.**
All non-commercial use of the Language is free and requires no
authorization beyond compliance with this license.

**4.2 Commercial Use: Authorization Required.**
Any Commercial Use of the Language requires the **prior written
authorization** of Julien Maurel. This includes but is not limited to:
- Selling products or services that incorporate the Language
- Using the Language in paid courses, workshops, or training programs
- Integrating the Language into commercial software or AI products
- Publishing books, guides, or materials about the Language for profit
- Creating paid applications or tools based on the Language
- Using the Language in advertising or marketing materials

**4.3 Revenue Sharing.**
Any authorized Commercial Use may be subject to a revenue sharing
agreement at the Creator's discretion. Terms will be negotiated on a
case-by-case basis.

**4.4 Exceptions.**
The following commercial activities do NOT require authorization:
- Using the Language in personal communication within a commercial context
  (e.g., speaking Syn'Tek at work)
- Mentioning or referencing the Language in commercial publications
  (journalism, reviews, etc.) under fair use
- Creating free, open-source tools that support the Language
  (with proper attribution)

**4.5 Contact for Commercial Licensing.**
For commercial use inquiries, contact: **Julien Maurel** via the official
Syn'Tek repository or through designated communication channels listed
in the repository.

---

## ARTICLE 5 — CONTRIBUTIONS

**5.1 Contribution License Grant.**
By submitting a Contribution to the Language (via Pull Request or any
other submission method), the Contributor irrevocably grants to
Julien Maurel:
- A **worldwide, perpetual, irrevocable, royalty-free, non-exclusive
  license** to use, modify, distribute, sublicense, and incorporate the
  Contribution into the Language
- The right to modify, adapt, or reject the Contribution at the Creator's
  sole discretion
- The right to credit or not credit the Contributor (though the Creator
  will make best efforts to acknowledge Contributors)

**5.2 No Ownership Transfer.**
Submitting a Contribution does NOT grant the Contributor any ownership
rights over:
- The Language as a whole
- Any part of the Language that existed before the Contribution
- The Syn'Tek name, brand, or intellectual property

**5.3 Contributor Credit.**
Contributors ("Primes") will be acknowledged in the project's
Contributors file or documentation at the Creator's discretion. This
acknowledgment does NOT imply co-ownership, co-creatorship, or any
intellectual property rights.

**5.4 Original Work.**
Contributors warrant that their Contributions are original work and do
not infringe on any third-party intellectual property rights. Contributors
are solely responsible for ensuring their Contributions are legally clean.

**5.5 Right of Removal.**
The Creator reserves the absolute right to remove, modify, or replace
any Contribution at any time, for any reason, without obligation to the
Contributor.

---

## ARTICLE 6 — RESTRICTIONS (What Users CANNOT Do)

Users and Contributors are strictly prohibited from:

**6.1 Claiming Creatorship.**
No person or entity may claim to have created, invented, designed, or
co-created the Syn'Tek Language. Julien Maurel is the sole creator.
Any false claim of creatorship constitutes a violation of this license
and may be subject to legal action.

**6.2 Claiming Ownership.**
No person or entity may claim ownership of the Language, in whole or in
part. The Language belongs exclusively to Julien Maurel.

**6.3 Removing Attribution.**
No person or entity may remove, obscure, or modify the Creator's name,
copyright notice, or this license from any copy or distribution of the
Language.

**6.4 Registering IP.**
No person or entity may:
- File trademark applications for "Syn'Tek" or variations thereof
- File patent applications covering the Language's syntax or methods
- File copyright registrations claiming authorship of the Language
- Register domain names using "Syn'Tek" or confusingly similar names
  without the Creator's explicit written authorization

**6.5 Misrepresentation.**
No person or entity may:
- Present a modified version as the official Language
- Imply endorsement by the Creator without authorization
- Use the Language's name or brand in a way that damages its reputation
- Create a competing language using substantially similar tokens and
  syntax without original creative contribution

**6.6 Sublicensing.**
No person or entity may sublicense the Language or grant rights to third
parties beyond what this license explicitly permits.

**6.7 Hostile Forking.**
No person or entity may fork the Language with the intent of:
- Replacing the official Language
- Claiming the fork as the "real" or "original" Syn'Tek
- Diverting the community from the official project
- Competing with the Creator's authority over the Language

---

## ARTICLE 7 — ENFORCEMENT & VIOLATIONS

**7.1 License Termination.**
Any violation of this license automatically and immediately terminates
the violator's rights under this license. Upon termination:
- The violator must immediately cease all use of the Language
- The violator must remove all copies and derivative works
- The violator must publicly retract any false claims

**7.2 Legal Action.**
The Creator reserves the right to pursue legal action against any
person or entity that violates this license, including but not limited
to claims for:
- Copyright infringement
- Trademark infringement
- Moral rights violation
- Unfair competition
- Damages and legal costs

**7.3 DMCA & Takedowns.**
The Creator reserves the right to issue DMCA takedown notices or
equivalent legal requests against any unauthorized use, distribution,
or misrepresentation of the Language on any platform, including but not
limited to GitHub, social media, websites, and application stores.

**7.4 Jurisdiction.**
This license shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the
laws of the **Republic of Mauritius**, without regard to its conflict of
law provisions. Any disputes arising from this license shall be subject
to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Mauritius.

**7.5 Good Faith Resolution.**
Before initiating legal proceedings, the Creator will make reasonable
efforts to resolve disputes through direct communication. Violators are
encouraged to contact the Creator promptly upon becoming aware of any
violation.

